1
00:00:16,394 --> 00:00:18,438
Blind date is Saturday at 7 PM

2
00:00:19,230 --> 00:00:20,899
Gangnam Station Exit 2

3
00:00:42,170 --> 00:00:44,130
I really enjoyed the lunch box

4
00:00:44,589 --> 00:00:47,676
But I can't eat Buldak

5
00:00:57,519 --> 00:00:59,354
Then what do you like?

6
00:01:00,647 --> 00:01:02,065
Carbo

7
00:01:03,358 --> 00:01:04,693
Carbo?

8
00:01:06,444 --> 00:01:08,071
Carbo Buldak?

9
00:01:09,531 --> 00:01:10,657
Yes

10
00:01:12,534 --> 00:01:14,661
That's still Buldak, isn't it

11
00:01:16,621 --> 00:01:18,832
Carbo is Carbo

12
00:01:31,219 --> 00:01:34,097
I'll buy you Carbo next time

13
00:01:36,474 --> 00:01:38,476
Next time?

14
00:01:43,314 --> 00:01:45,316
If you don't want to, then never mind

15
00:01:46,776 --> 00:01:48,987
I didn't say I didn't want to

16
00:02:16,806 --> 00:02:17,974
What was that?

17
00:02:20,310 --> 00:02:21,269
What?

18
00:02:22,062 --> 00:02:23,438
Just now, you

19
00:02:23,772 --> 00:02:25,565
...went "Heheh."

20
00:02:26,274 --> 00:02:27,692
Hey, I did not

21
00:02:27,692 --> 00:02:29,027
Yes, you did

22
00:02:31,154 --> 00:02:33,448
It's been so long since I last saw Kim So-hee laugh?

23
00:02:34,657 --> 00:02:36,076
Am I not allowed to laugh?

24
00:02:36,284 --> 00:02:39,120
No, it's just that you always look so miserable

25
00:02:39,788 --> 00:02:41,122
Hey, but what's this?

26
00:02:41,122 --> 00:02:42,874
Are you talking to someone?

27
00:02:45,293 --> 00:02:46,211
No

28
00:02:46,920 --> 00:02:48,171
Really?

29
00:02:48,755 --> 00:02:49,798
I said no

30
00:02:52,175 --> 00:02:52,884
Okay

31
00:02:52,884 --> 00:02:55,470
So you're going on the blind date on Saturday, right?

32
00:02:56,471 --> 00:02:57,347
Ah..

33
00:02:59,390 --> 00:03:00,558
Yeah, I'll go

34
00:03:00,767 --> 00:03:03,228
Oh, for once?

35
00:03:03,436 --> 00:03:05,939
You always made excuses and refused to go

36
00:03:06,731 --> 00:03:09,400
I'm just going to check it out

37
00:03:11,694 --> 00:03:13,154
Kim So-hee?

38
00:03:15,156 --> 00:03:16,574
Eat your food

39
00:03:25,834 --> 00:03:28,169
[Are you working overtime today too?]

40
00:03:44,310 --> 00:03:45,728
[Carbo Buldak Bokkeumyeon]

41
00:04:11,921 --> 00:04:13,590
Why is this in the fridge

42
00:04:13,590 --> 00:04:15,466
...right next to the beer?

43
00:04:18,261 --> 00:04:20,388
It seems like someone left it there?

44
00:04:29,063 --> 00:04:30,857
Do you want to eat it together?

45
00:04:33,443 --> 00:04:34,819
I'm currently on duty

46
00:04:37,155 --> 00:04:38,740
What time do you get off work?

47
00:04:40,283 --> 00:04:41,576
12 o'clock

48
00:04:46,623 --> 00:04:48,124
30 minutes left, then

49
00:04:50,960 --> 00:04:52,337
I'll wait outside

50
00:05:25,787 --> 00:05:26,621
Whew

51
00:05:26,621 --> 00:05:27,747
It's spicy

52
00:05:30,375 --> 00:05:32,252
Carbo isn't that spicy

53
00:05:33,544 --> 00:05:34,671
It is spicy

54
00:05:36,756 --> 00:05:38,633
If you can't eat it, I'll eat it

55
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:42,387
Who said I can't eat it?

56
00:05:51,980 --> 00:05:52,355
Huh?

57
00:05:54,232 --> 00:05:54,607
Huh?

58
00:05:56,359 --> 00:05:57,652
Why are you laughing?

59
00:05:58,820 --> 00:05:59,946
Just because

60
00:06:10,039 --> 00:06:12,750
Ji-eun, are you a student?

61
00:06:14,168 --> 00:06:16,212
Yes, I'm taking a break from school

62
00:06:17,755 --> 00:06:19,132
Which university?

63
00:06:21,009 --> 00:06:22,176
Seohan University

64
00:06:23,678 --> 00:06:25,054
Ah, Seohan University

65
00:06:25,638 --> 00:06:27,765
What year did you enter?

66
00:06:27,765 --> 00:06:29,017
Class of '24

67
00:06:31,352 --> 00:06:33,479
So, twenty-two?

68
00:06:33,938 --> 00:06:34,731
Yes

69
00:06:35,648 --> 00:06:37,358
I'm twenty-seven

70
00:06:39,193 --> 00:06:40,528
Then you're my Unnie

71
00:06:44,115 --> 00:06:46,909
I can call you Unnie, right?

72
00:06:48,369 --> 00:06:49,329
Of course

73
00:06:49,329 --> 00:06:50,455
I'll speak casually to you too

74
00:06:56,044 --> 00:06:58,588
Unnie, is work fun?

75
00:07:01,591 --> 00:07:03,634
If it were fun, would I be coming here

76
00:07:03,634 --> 00:07:05,011
...to drink every single day?

77
00:07:05,428 --> 00:07:06,679
You still might

78
00:07:08,097 --> 00:07:08,765
What?

79
00:07:10,224 --> 00:07:11,100
Drink

80
00:07:12,477 --> 00:07:13,686
Because there are plenty of people

81
00:07:13,686 --> 00:07:15,688
...who drink simply because they like the taste

82
00:07:19,484 --> 00:07:20,485
That's not me

83
00:07:22,820 --> 00:07:25,490
Then why come here every day?

84
00:07:28,451 --> 00:07:29,535
Well..

85
00:07:30,161 --> 00:07:31,579
Out of habit

86
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:35,416
Habit?

87
00:07:37,502 --> 00:07:38,211
Yeah

88
00:07:51,849 --> 00:07:53,059
Hold on..

89
00:07:53,393 --> 00:07:55,353
You have something on your face

90
00:07:57,063 --> 00:07:58,064
Pardon?

91
00:08:52,034 --> 00:08:54,662
My hobby is hiking

92
00:08:54,662 --> 00:08:57,039
So I go climbing every weekend

93
00:08:59,333 --> 00:09:01,377
Unnie, what do you do on weekends?

94
00:09:02,044 --> 00:09:03,754
There's a mountain called Gyeryongsan

95
00:09:03,754 --> 00:09:06,883
In fall, the leaves are art?

96
00:09:07,300 --> 00:09:08,176
Ah, but

97
00:09:08,176 --> 00:09:09,427
It's a bit steep, so

98
00:09:09,427 --> 00:09:10,928
...it might be a little tough for you

99
00:09:11,220 --> 00:09:14,348
Achasan is too low, so it might be boring

100
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:15,349
Oh!

101
00:09:15,349 --> 00:09:17,810
Bukhansan is pretty good for beginners

102
00:09:18,019 --> 00:09:19,061
Would you like to go there together sometime?

103
00:09:20,021 --> 00:09:20,980
Ah..

104
00:09:22,148 --> 00:09:25,651
I don't really like hiking, so

105
00:09:26,402 --> 00:09:27,403
Ah..

106
00:09:27,403 --> 00:09:29,238
Then what do you like to do?

107
00:09:32,366 --> 00:09:33,409
Convenience stores?

108
00:09:35,161 --> 00:09:35,745
Pardon?

109
00:09:37,580 --> 00:09:39,123
At convenience stores..

110
00:09:39,123 --> 00:09:40,791
...I like drinking beer

111
00:09:40,791 --> 00:09:41,667
Drinking alone

112
00:09:42,168 --> 00:09:42,752
Ah..

113
00:09:42,752 --> 00:09:43,461
Drinking?

114
00:09:44,045 --> 00:09:45,254
I like drinking too

115
00:09:50,468 --> 00:09:51,719
How was it? How was it?

116
00:10:05,399 --> 00:10:06,275
Oh

117
00:10:07,151 --> 00:10:07,985
How was it?

118
00:10:08,986 --> 00:10:10,530
Just so-so

119
00:10:11,364 --> 00:10:13,241
What do you mean, "just so-so"?

120
00:10:13,241 --> 00:10:14,325
Wasn't he decent?

121
00:10:15,743 --> 00:10:17,245
He likes hiking

122
00:10:18,162 --> 00:10:19,038
So?

123
00:10:20,748 --> 00:10:22,625
I hate hiking

124
00:10:22,792 --> 00:10:23,417
What?

125
00:10:25,711 --> 00:10:27,838
I just didn't feel any spark

126
00:10:29,048 --> 00:10:29,882
Sigh..

127
00:10:30,299 --> 00:10:32,802
What kind of person are you even attracted to?

128
00:10:33,177 --> 00:10:34,637
He's really decent, you know

129
00:10:35,096 --> 00:10:36,597
Give him one more chance and meet him again

130
00:10:39,141 --> 00:10:40,226
Hello?

131
00:10:40,476 --> 00:10:41,477
Kim So-hee?

132
00:10:41,602 --> 00:10:42,395
Kim So-hee?

133
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:44,313
Whatever, I'm hanging up

134
00:11:04,458 --> 00:11:05,960
Hello, Unnie

135
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:06,961
Hi

136
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:15,177
You're wearing perfume

137
00:11:15,886 --> 00:11:17,179
And your makeup is quite heavy

138
00:11:19,515 --> 00:11:20,641
Ah..

139
00:11:21,434 --> 00:11:23,477
I had plans today

140
00:11:26,856 --> 00:11:29,525
You didn't read Kakao, so I thought you slept

141
00:11:30,484 --> 00:11:31,944
I guess you went on a blind date?

142
00:11:35,448 --> 00:11:37,116
How did you know?

143
00:11:38,826 --> 00:11:39,744
Usually

144
00:11:39,744 --> 00:11:42,038
...you usually look totally done with life

145
00:11:45,791 --> 00:11:46,792
But..

146
00:11:46,792 --> 00:11:49,003
Today, you look like a decent, neat person?

147
00:11:55,968 --> 00:11:57,762
What time do you finish today?

148
00:11:58,763 --> 00:12:00,431
10 PM on weekends

149
00:12:04,018 --> 00:12:05,519
There are 10 minutes left

150
00:12:06,187 --> 00:12:07,480
Want to grab a drink together?

151
00:12:09,315 --> 00:12:09,982
Pardon?

152
00:12:11,776 --> 00:12:13,986
Ah, today..

153
00:12:13,986 --> 00:12:17,156
...it's not a day to drink alone

154
00:12:18,949 --> 00:12:20,451
The blind date..

155
00:12:20,993 --> 00:12:22,453
...I guess it didn't go well?

156
00:12:30,461 --> 00:12:32,505
Then let's buy one more can

157
00:12:33,506 --> 00:12:35,966
On days like this, you should drink a bit more

158
00:13:05,955 --> 00:13:07,123
No, wait..

159
00:13:08,666 --> 00:13:10,000
At my blind date today

160
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:12,253
Do you know what happened?

161
00:13:14,797 --> 00:13:15,923
He

162
00:13:15,923 --> 00:13:18,509
...asked me what my hobby is

163
00:13:19,176 --> 00:13:22,263
I almost said I was coming here

164
00:13:24,598 --> 00:13:25,850
Really?

165
00:13:27,309 --> 00:13:28,477
Yes

166
00:13:28,936 --> 00:13:30,146
I made up an excuse saying I like beer

167
00:13:30,146 --> 00:13:31,272
...though

168
00:13:36,485 --> 00:13:38,070
During your blind date

169
00:13:38,654 --> 00:13:39,864
...you thought of me?

170
00:13:48,456 --> 00:13:48,914
Hey

171
00:13:49,373 --> 00:13:51,375
Why would I think of you?

172
00:13:51,375 --> 00:13:53,252
I thought of the convenience store

173
00:13:56,213 --> 00:13:57,339
That's basically the same thing

174
00:14:00,259 --> 00:14:02,219
Why do you like the convenience store so much anyway?

175
00:14:05,097 --> 00:14:06,348
Well..

176
00:14:07,725 --> 00:14:09,894
Because it feels like the day is finally ending

177
00:14:18,235 --> 00:14:19,945
Is that really all?

178
00:14:22,823 --> 00:14:24,408
Of course it is

179
00:14:28,704 --> 00:14:29,830
Unnie

180
00:14:33,417 --> 00:14:35,085
After I got your post-it note

181
00:14:35,085 --> 00:14:37,087
...and when I was adding you on KakaoTalk

182
00:14:38,839 --> 00:14:41,050
...I kept hesitating

183
00:14:43,052 --> 00:14:44,512
Why?

184
00:14:46,222 --> 00:14:48,307
You're a regular customer, after all

185
00:14:48,307 --> 00:14:50,017
I was worried it might get awkward

186
00:14:53,145 --> 00:14:54,438
But?

187
00:14:56,690 --> 00:14:58,567
In the end, I did it anyway

188
00:14:59,235 --> 00:15:01,070
And I even talked to you first

189
00:15:05,533 --> 00:15:08,118
Why do you think I did that?

190
00:15:13,499 --> 00:15:14,792
Ah

191
00:15:15,668 --> 00:15:18,379
The beer has lost all its carbonation

192
00:15:20,589 --> 00:15:22,091
I should head out first

193
00:15:22,091 --> 00:15:24,260
I have to go to work tomorrow too
